00:02:17,100 --> 00:02:22,400
    
    

18
00:02:37,060 --> 00:02:38,760
Dad.

19
00:02:39,700 --> 00:02:45,000
The new table has arrived, so why are you still eating here? Why not eat there?

20
00:02:45,000 --> 00:02:47,400
What if that nice table gets scorched?

21
00:02:47,400 --> 00:02:52,100
What? Isn't the table meant for eating?

22
00:02:52,100 --> 00:02:55,300
Afraid of scorching it? Are you looking down on the designer?

23
00:02:55,300 --> 00:02:57,400
It's also not easy to clean if it gets dirty.

24
00:02:57,400 --> 00:03:01,100
It was designed by my son-in-law. We should cherish it, right?

25
00:03:01,100 --> 00:03:03,300
How's your accounting going? Making any money?

26
00:03:03,300 --> 00:03:06,500
Not bad. We should be able to break even this way.

27
00:03:06,500 --> 00:03:10,400
That's good then. What about Lin Tuo?

28
00:03:10,400 --> 00:03:13,500
I don't know. He's not answering his phone.

29
00:03:20,200 --> 00:03:24,300
 I've arrived home. Too tired. I'm going to sleep now. Let's talk tomorrow. 

30
00:03:24,300 --> 00:03:29,800
How tiring can it be to make a call after you're already back?

31
00:03:29,800 --> 00:03:32,200
What did you do to be so tired?

32
00:03:32,200 --> 00:03:35,200
Isn't he busy? He did reply to your WeChat messages, didn't he?

33
00:03:35,200 --> 00:03:38,100
Why be so fussy?

34
00:03:42,600 --> 00:03:46,700
I'm not replying. So pissed.

35
00:04:15,400 --> 00:04:17,200
   

36
00:04:53,600 --> 00:04:57,400
Why did you sleep on the sofa without changing your clothes?

37
00:04:57,400 --> 00:05:00,200
I was too tired and didn't want to go to bed.

38
00:05:00,800 --> 00:05:03,700
What time is it? Aren't you going to work?

39
00:05:03,700 --> 00:05:05,400
Yes.

40
00:05:10,240 --> 00:05:16,120
We haven't seen each other for a week, but I can't see the eager anticipation in your eyes.

41
00:05:16,120 --> 00:05:18,290
It's in my mind.

42
00:05:21,700 --> 00:05:26,300
What's that smell on your clothes? A smell of hospital disinfectant.

43
00:05:27,900 --> 00:05:30,000
Really? I've just changed.

44
00:05:30,000 --> 00:05:31,900
Yes, there is.

45
00:05:33,300 --> 00:05:35,800
I'll go clean up.

46
00:05:38,079 --> 00:05:40,299
How's your business these past few days?

47
00:05:40,299 --> 00:05:42,200
It is doing pretty well.

48
00:05:42,200 --> 00:05:44,300
We've released a new product now.

49
00:05:44,300 --> 00:05:46,800
It's on sale at half price, and the reviews are especially good.

50
00:05:46,800 --> 00:05:49,200
There are also so many delivery orders

51
00:05:49,200 --> 00:05:52,700
 that sometimes, I can't even attend to the customers in the store. 

52
00:05:52,700 --> 00:05:55,200
 I'm preparing to hire someone now. 

53
00:05:55,200 --> 00:06:01,700
And your buddy, Chen Guangpu, is really clumsy, making Xindi even busier.

54
00:06:01,700 --> 00:06:04,100
 Right, I interviewed a kid the other day. 

55
00:06:04,100 --> 00:06:06,300
 I found him particularly cute. I quite liked him. 

56
00:06:06,300 --> 00:06:09,100
 Curly-haired. He's called A'Bao. 

57
00:06:13,940 --> 00:06:18,800
   

58
00:06:18,800 --> 00:06:22,400
This is the Pengyu project book. All six products have been completed.

59
00:06:22,400 --> 00:06:24,600
Once you sign, I'll file it.

60
00:06:24,600 --> 00:06:29,400
All right. Somebody from Jingtian will visit today. Have a meeting with them.

61
00:06:29,400 --> 00:06:32,700
Get an idea of what they want, and you'll be in charge.

62
00:06:34,800 --> 00:06:38,200
Chief Designer, I have something to tell you.

63
00:06:38,200 --> 00:06:39,800
Go ahead.

64
00:06:42,100 --> 00:06:46,900
I might not be able to be a designer in the future.

65
00:06:52,019 --> 00:06:53,719
The reason?

66
00:06:56,700 --> 00:07:01,800
My right hand might not be able to draw anymore.

67
00:07:11,800 --> 00:07:14,400
The basic situation is like this. 
    

68
00:07:14,400 --> 00:07:19,700
This menu lists some of my coffee-making tips and recipes.

69
00:07:19,700 --> 00:07:23,000
Right now, there are four basic types of coffee.

70
00:07:23,000 --> 00:07:25,800
That is, Americano, latte, pour-over, and cold brew.

71
00:07:25,800 --> 00:07:28,000
Just make them with the normal ratios.

72
00:07:28,000 --> 00:07:32,200
There are also two seasonal drinks that we change regularly.

73
00:07:32,200 --> 00:07:35,400
It's coconut and soy milk pudding this month.

74
00:07:35,400 --> 00:07:38,400
Feel free to bring up your ideas and discuss them with me.

75
00:07:38,400 --> 00:07:40,300
Okay.

76
00:07:40,300 --> 00:07:44,000
Although the shop is small, there's actually quite a lot to do.

77
00:07:44,000 --> 00:07:45,800
Previously, my friend helped me.

78
00:07:45,800 --> 00:07:48,400
But now she's too busy with her live-streaming work.

79
00:07:48,400 --> 00:07:52,400
We work together, so the division of work might not be very clear.

80
00:07:52,400 --> 00:07:55,200
I can do anything. Drinks, coffee, cakes.

81
00:07:55,200 --> 00:07:57,400
I'm also very good at cleaning, and I'm strong.

82
00:07:57,400 --> 00:08:00,600
- All right, then welcome to HW Cafe. 
 - Thank you, Boss.

83
00:08:00,600 --> 00:08:03,500
You don't have to call me boss. Just call me Xiao Que.

84
00:08:03,500 --> 00:08:06,700
You're 22, one year older than me, so I'll call you Sister Que.

85
00:08:06,700 --> 00:08:08,300
Okay, Brother.

86
00:08:08,300 --> 00:08:09,600
Welcome to HW Cafe.

87
00:08:09,600 --> 00:08:12,900
- Welcome. 
 - What would you like to order?

88
00:08:18,400 --> 00:08:20,300
Is it confirmed?

89
00:08:22,100 --> 00:08:24,600
The screening results aren't out yet.

90
00:08:24,600 --> 00:08:29,200
The doctor said it was hard to diagnose my condition directly.

91
00:08:29,200 --> 00:08:31,600
We have to rule things out one by one.

92
00:08:32,625 --> 00:08:35,285
That means, it could be a tumor.

93
00:08:40,400 --> 00:08:45,600
Who would have thought that one day, they would hope to have a tumor?

94
00:08:48,300 --> 00:08:53,000
But now, I'm even eagerly hoping

95
00:08:53,599 --> 00:08:58,259
it's a tumor or cancer.

96
00:09:00,000 --> 00:09:01,900
That way, there might still be hope.

97
00:09:01,900 --> 00:09:06,200
It's just your right hand that's not working well, right? You still can move it.

98
00:09:06,200 --> 00:09:10,000
Anyway, if it doesn't work, there's still the left. If one day...

99
00:09:12,910 --> 00:09:15,770
We'll get a lot of projects. Our team will get a lot of projects.

100
00:09:15,770 --> 00:09:19,800
Even if you can't draw anymore, you can do other things. What do you want to be?

101
00:09:23,900 --> 00:09:26,000
Your assistant.

102
00:09:28,800 --> 00:09:31,100
I still have my left hand, don't I?

103
00:09:31,900 --> 00:09:34,800
Right, being an assistant would be good.

104
00:09:34,800 --> 00:09:36,400
I especially need a good assistant.

105
00:09:36,400 --> 00:09:40,700
You'll be the assistant and continue working. What's the issue?

106
00:09:43,000 --> 00:09:45,319
Thank you, Chief Designer.

107
00:09:45,319 --> 00:09:51,322
Let's go to the meeting. Get back to work.

108
00:09:51,322 --> 00:09:53,110
Chief Designer.

109
00:09:56,100 --> 00:09:58,400
Can you do me a favor?

110
00:09:59,000 --> 00:10:00,600
Go ahead.

111
00:10:02,319 --> 00:10:06,979
I haven't told anyone about my illness.

112
00:10:07,699 --> 00:10:09,819
You're the first one.

113
00:10:11,400 --> 00:10:13,700
Can you keep it a secret for me?

114
00:10:16,000 --> 00:10:18,100
   

115
00:10:21,879 --> 00:10:26,234
Huo Sheng, you'll be in charge of the Jingtian project.

116
00:10:26,234 --> 00:10:30,299
- Okay. 
 - Lin Tuo, set aside what you're handling and work with me on the Yaoshi project.

117
00:10:30,299 --> 00:10:33,180
This afternoon, the people from Jingtian are coming for a meeting.

118
00:10:33,180 --> 00:10:36,200
Huo Sheng, Peng Qianfan, you'll be in charge.

119
00:10:36,739 --> 00:10:39,679
Lin Tuo, get the Yaoshi project book done.

120
00:10:39,679 --> 00:10:41,400
Okay.

121
00:10:48,639 --> 00:10:51,539
Lin Tuo, why are you doing an assistant's work again?

122
00:10:51,539 --> 00:10:54,479
Is it because you're too prominent?

123
00:10:54,479 --> 00:11:00,039
No, I asked Chief Designer to mentor me more.

124
00:11:00,039 --> 00:11:03,179
I begged him for a long time before he agreed.

125
00:11:03,179 --> 00:11:05,879
I knew it. He isn't that kind of person.

126
00:11:05,879 --> 00:11:07,499
What's for lunch?

127
00:11:07,499 --> 00:11:09,419
I'll order in a bit.

128
00:11:09,419 --> 00:11:11,210
   

129
00:11:19,019 --> 00:11:20,899
 The exhibition is such a good opportunity. 

130
00:11:20,899 --> 00:11:23,039
I went to apply for it specifically.

131
00:11:23,039 --> 00:11:26,359
Why are you stopping him from going? I didn't ask you to go.

132
00:11:26,359 --> 00:11:29,630
- I'm the boss of my team. 
 - Wei Haiyang.

133
00:11:30,179 --> 00:11:35,399
Don't tell me you are afraid that Lin Tuo will outshine you.

134
00:11:35,399 --> 00:11:37,119
Am I that kind of person?

135
00:11:37,119 --> 00:11:40,699
What are you actually thinking now?

136
00:11:40,699 --> 00:11:43,820
If he wins an award, it will benefit the firm.

137
00:11:43,820 --> 00:11:47,465
You're aware of how many orders are placed at the exhibition each year.

138
00:11:47,465 --> 00:11:49,990
Even if he doesn't win,

139
00:11:49,990 --> 00:11:53,099
what's wrong with a newcomer getting some experience?

140
00:11:53,099 --> 00:11:57,359
Our team is too busy. Let's change the person.

141
00:11:58,700 --> 00:12:04,379
Besides, just because a green young man designed a few small products that sold well,

142
00:12:04,379 --> 00:12:08,879
is it necessary to put him on a pedestal? I'm going to temper him before he gets too cocky.

143
00:12:08,879 --> 00:12:13,099
He is an assistant now, not a designer. I have the final say.

144
00:12:13,999 --> 00:12:15,699
You're just narrow-minded.

145
00:12:15,699 --> 00:12:19,059
See? That is the epitome of being narrow-minded.

146
00:12:20,719 --> 00:12:22,639
You think you're broad-minded?

147
00:12:22,639 --> 00:12:25,139
I'm more broad-minded than you.

148
00:12:29,459 --> 00:12:33,179
Director Qian, this is the new design draft. Please have a look.

149
00:12:59,716 --> 00:13:05,088
   

150
00:13:18,799 --> 00:13:20,939
Here, coffee beans.

151
00:13:20,939 --> 00:13:23,139
May I have another pack? I'm going to an exhibition next week.

152
00:13:23,139 --> 00:13:26,919
- All right. A'Bao, another bag of coffee beans. 
 - All right.

153
00:13:26,919 --> 00:13:29,699
An exhibition? Where is it?

154
00:13:29,699 --> 00:13:32,019
The Young Designers Exhibition in Shanghai.

155
00:13:32,019 --> 00:13:36,879
When can Lin Tuo attend it?

156
00:13:36,879 --> 00:13:38,919
He was supposed to go this time.

157
00:13:38,919 --> 00:13:42,480
I just called him to talk about this. He didn't answer.

158
00:13:42,480 --> 00:13:45,719
Why didn't he go? Was he not allowed?

159
00:13:45,719 --> 00:13:48,379
It seems that their team leader didn't let him go.

160
00:13:48,379 --> 00:13:50,559
And Lin Tuo wasn't promoted to designer this time.

161
00:13:50,559 --> 00:13:54,279
I just went to Director Qian's office and heard them talking about it.

162
00:13:54,279 --> 00:13:56,839
I don't know if Lin Tuo is aware.

163
00:13:56,839 --> 00:13:59,479
Did he offend their team leader or something?

164
00:13:59,479 --> 00:14:02,459
But he has a good relationship with his leader.

165
00:14:02,459 --> 00:14:06,559
He often comes here for coffee. I've never heard him say that.

166
00:14:06,559 --> 00:14:09,759
I'm not too clear on the specifics.

167
00:14:09,759 --> 00:14:12,199
Maybe their team has other plans.

168
00:14:12,199 --> 00:14:16,019
They are working on a lot of projects now and have to work overtime every day.

169
00:14:16,019 --> 00:14:20,379
Yes. Now you're off work and he is still busy.

170
00:14:21,619 --> 00:14:23,420
Aren't Guangpu and your bestie here?

171
00:14:23,420 --> 00:14:24,759
They'll be back soon.

172
00:14:24,759 --> 00:14:28,319
- Sister Que, it's ready. 
 - Okay.

173
00:14:28,319 --> 00:14:29,780
Here, coffee beans.

174
00:14:29,780 --> 00:14:31,339
- Okay, thanks. 
 - Not at all.

175
00:14:31,339 --> 00:14:33,799
After I come back, let's have a meal together with Lin Tuo.

176
00:14:33,799 --> 00:14:37,419
- Sure. Bye. Take care. 
 - I'm off. Bye.

177
00:14:51,292 --> 00:14:53,290
   

178
00:15:01,479 --> 00:15:02,699
Xiao Tuo.

179
00:15:02,699 --> 00:15:05,839
You're at home. Why didn't you drop by the cafe?

180
00:15:05,839 --> 00:15:09,179
After I finished work, it was too late. The cafe was already closed.

181
00:15:09,179 --> 00:15:11,359
I still had some documents to look up so I went home first.

182
00:15:11,359 --> 00:15:13,199
Have you eaten yet?

183
00:15:13,199 --> 00:15:15,119
I'm not hungry.

184
00:15:16,379 --> 00:15:21,919
Xiao Tuo, did something happen to you at work?

185
00:15:23,239 --> 00:15:25,439
No, what's wrong?

186
00:15:25,439 --> 00:15:30,379
Why didn't your leader let you attend the Young Designers Exhibition?

187
00:15:31,339 --> 00:15:33,459
Who told you that?

188
00:15:33,459 --> 00:15:36,539
Senior came to buy coffee beans and mentioned it today.

189
00:15:36,539 --> 00:15:41,219
He said you were supposed to go, but then you weren't allowed. Why?

190
00:15:42,699 --> 00:15:44,619
How does he know that?

191
00:15:44,619 --> 00:15:49,479
He said he overheard it in Director Qian's office.

192
00:15:49,479 --> 00:15:51,739
I'm asking you. Do you know about that?

193
00:15:51,739 --> 00:15:54,520
Are you still kept in the dark or what?

194
00:15:55,139 --> 00:15:56,464
No.

195
00:15:56,464 --> 00:15:58,980
No? He has heard about it.

196
00:15:58,980 --> 00:16:01,039
Did they not notify you at all?

197
00:16:01,039 --> 00:16:04,719
Did you not get promoted to designer either? Why?

198
00:16:04,719 --> 00:16:08,219
Can't you stop prying from others all the time?

199
00:16:08,219 --> 00:16:10,139
They don't even know what happened.

200
00:16:10,139 --> 00:16:13,299
What do you mean by "others"? Am I "others" too?

201
00:16:13,299 --> 00:16:15,699
Why don't you tell me anything anymore?

202
00:16:15,699 --> 00:16:18,339
Those are my work matters. What do you want me to tell you?

203
00:16:18,339 --> 00:16:21,284
You're not my boss. Do I have to report my work to you too?

204
00:16:21,284 --> 00:16:24,120
Wait, what do you mean by "report"?

205
00:16:24,120 --> 00:16:26,499
Am I not even allowed to ask about your work?

206
00:16:26,499 --> 00:16:29,739
Well, what do you want me to say about my work?

207
00:16:29,739 --> 00:16:34,620
Lin Tuo, are you silly? You've been fooled by your leader. Can't you see that?

208
00:16:34,620 --> 00:16:39,379
It's clear that your design has made you stand out, but your leader doesn't want to see that.

209
00:16:39,379 --> 00:16:42,379
You should already be a designer. Why didn't they promote you?

210
00:16:42,379 --> 00:16:45,599
Just like before, still doing odds and ends as an assistant. Are you foolish or what?

211
00:16:45,599 --> 00:16:49,739
I don't want to be a designer. It has nothing to do with my leader.

212
00:16:49,739 --> 00:16:51,919
I don't want to attend.

213
00:16:51,919 --> 00:16:53,179
Why?

214
00:16:53,179 --> 00:16:57,099
Why? Why must I be a designer?

215
00:16:57,099 --> 00:17:00,759
Won't it work if I don't become a designer? Does it mean I can't live on?

216
00:17:00,759 --> 00:17:02,280
What do you mean by this?

217
00:17:02,280 --> 00:17:04,979
Haven't you always wanted to be a designer since you were young?

218
00:17:04,979 --> 00:17:07,118
Didn't you go to Ji Jia to become a designer?

219
00:17:07,118 --> 00:17:09,198
Now you're telling me you don't want to be a designer?

220
00:17:09,198 --> 00:17:11,519
Are you sick or something?

221
00:17:12,538 --> 00:17:15,579
Yes, I must be sick.

222
00:17:16,740 --> 00:17:19,701
Lin Tuo, what are you doing?

223
00:17:22,899 --> 00:17:27,258
Can we two not argue over this matter right now?

224
00:17:27,258 --> 00:17:29,559
Did I come here to argue with you?

225
00:17:29,559 --> 00:17:35,020
I worry that you've been badly treated in the office. You mean I ran over here to have an argument with you?

226
00:17:35,020 --> 00:17:36,859
No, that's not what it was.

227
00:17:36,859 --> 00:17:40,319
I mean, I have my own work plans. I know what I'm doing.

228
00:17:40,319 --> 00:17:42,339
Can't I just further develop and improve myself?

229
00:17:42,339 --> 00:17:46,559
Why are you trying to dictate my choices over this matter, forcing me to do as you say?

230
00:17:46,559 --> 00:17:48,899
Do I have to tell you everything and do what you want?

231
00:17:48,899 --> 00:17:51,999
Now you're even questioning me because I don't want to be a designer.

232
00:17:51,999 --> 00:17:55,579
The work has made me tired and crazy. I worked overtime all day and didn't even get to eat.

233
00:17:55,579 --> 00:17:59,579
But you are now confronting me with your assumptions. What exactly do you want from me?

234
00:18:01,159 --> 00:18:05,559
You feel so aggrieved? Why didn't you say so?

235
00:18:12,999 --> 00:18:16,199
- Where are you going? 
 - None of your business.

236
00:18:41,159 --> 00:18:44,019
- He hasn't called you? 
 - No.

237
00:18:44,019 --> 00:18:47,216
- Not even a WeChat message? 
 - No.

238
00:18:48,359 --> 00:18:51,959
How dare he? The designer title has gone to his head?

239
00:18:51,959 --> 00:18:55,199
What designer? He hasn't become one yet.

240
00:18:55,199 --> 00:18:57,099
He told me he was not going to be a designer anymore.

241
00:18:57,099 --> 00:19:01,930
I don't know what's wrong with him.

242
00:19:02,539 --> 00:19:04,210
Sit.

243
00:19:04,799 --> 00:19:08,579
Lin Tuo wasn't like this before. Could he have been set up?

244
00:19:08,579 --> 00:19:11,519
I'm telling you, it's dangerous for newcomers to stand out.

245
00:19:11,519 --> 00:19:15,979
How long has he been in the firm? With his big poster hung up, surely someone's jealous.

246
00:19:15,979 --> 00:19:18,999
His leader looks like a sly old fox.

247
00:19:18,999 --> 00:19:22,799
Didn't he offend an old woman last time? They are the leaders.

248
00:19:22,799 --> 00:19:25,599
They wouldn't let a green man call the shots. They would target him.

249
00:19:25,599 --> 00:19:29,459
That's exactly what I said to him. He got mad at me

250
00:19:29,459 --> 00:19:33,159
and said I was the one with issues and conspiracy theories.

251
00:19:33,159 --> 00:19:35,699
Lin Tuo is just naive.

252
00:19:35,699 --> 00:19:38,799
He can't discern people's intentions at all.

253
00:19:39,859 --> 00:19:41,804
Look at Chen Guangpu.

254
00:19:41,804 --> 00:19:44,319
Still holding the phone with a silly smile.

255
00:19:44,319 --> 00:19:49,099
He told me he was chatting up a girl who just returned from abroad and spoke four languages.

256
00:19:49,099 --> 00:19:53,199
I asked him, "What does she do? A tour guide? What can you talk about?"

257
00:19:53,199 --> 00:19:58,919
Right after they met, he got dragged to a shopping mall and bought her a limited edition perfume.

258
00:19:58,919 --> 00:20:02,699
Look at him, still grinning there. Idiot.

259
00:20:02,699 --> 00:20:07,279
I can tell at a glance she's not a good girl. He's to be duped.

260
00:20:08,299 --> 00:20:11,479
Could there be something else going on with Lin Tuo?

261
00:20:11,479 --> 00:20:13,099
What?

262
00:20:13,099 --> 00:20:16,299
Lin Tuo has such a good temper. Did he really fight with you before?

263
00:20:16,299 --> 00:20:22,059
Is the work issue really the reason?

264
00:20:23,519 --> 00:20:27,320
I don't know. He's been distracted lately.

265
00:20:27,320 --> 00:20:31,239
Last night, as soon as I entered, he closed the lid of his tablet.

266
00:20:31,239 --> 00:20:32,939
That's it. He's having an affair.

267
00:20:32,939 --> 00:20:34,880
Impossible. Lin Tuo can't be having an affair.

268
00:20:34,880 --> 00:20:38,619
Really? Check his phone. There must be something.

269
00:20:38,619 --> 00:20:42,119
It's most likely the one working with him, the one named Hong, Lu, or something.

270
00:20:42,119 --> 00:20:46,259
Huang Xiaolu often comes. I know her. She's really nice.

271
00:20:46,259 --> 00:20:48,339
I believe Lin Tuo.

272
00:20:48,339 --> 00:20:52,039
You're stupid. Hopeless.

273
00:20:52,039 --> 00:20:55,260
I'd like some juice to replenish vitamins.

274
00:20:55,260 --> 00:20:58,239
Download an anti-fraud app to prevent pig-butchering scams.

275
00:20:58,239 --> 00:21:00,299
What? Who is a pig?

276
00:21:00,299 --> 00:21:02,939
Who else could it be? You.

277
00:21:02,939 --> 00:21:04,910
I just...

278
00:21:05,710 --> 00:21:07,190
You...

279
00:21:09,199 --> 00:21:13,359
Slow in the head and speech. Idiot.

280
00:21:17,670 --> 00:21:22,950
   

281
00:21:31,640 --> 00:21:35,725
Sister Que, I've finished cleaning inside. We can lock up now.

282
00:21:35,725 --> 00:21:38,120
You can leave. I'll lock up in a bit.

283
00:21:38,120 --> 00:21:40,365
Okay, I'm off. See you tomorrow.

284
00:21:40,365 --> 00:21:42,850
See you tomorrow, bye.

285
00:21:42,850 --> 00:21:44,860
   

286
00:21:49,320 --> 00:21:52,260
   

287
